Job description 1:

Requirements:
-Ability to lead strategic engagements across policy areas including energy, chemicals, taxation, trade.
-Strong capability to monitor, analyse, and interpret political, economic, and regulatory developments.
-Expertise in designing and implementing advocacy plans aligned to business priorities.
-Experience advising senior leadership on geopolitical, public policy, and regulatory matters.
-Strong collaboration skills for coordinating with local, regional, and global internal teams.
-Ability to build and maintain relationships with government bodies, trade associations, academia, and influencers.
-Proficiency in delivering policy updates, briefings, and strategic insights for leadership.
-Strong political acumen and ability to navigate complex regulatory and political environments.
-Excellent interpersonal and communication skills, with proficiency in Hindi, English, and one additional Indian language.
-Flexibility to participate in policy meetings and events beyond standard work hours.
Over and Above:
-Established relationships with key decision-makers in central government.
-Strong ownership mindset and solution-oriented strategic thinking.
-Experience in policy analysis, advisory roles, and advocacy-related work.

