-Skills in preparing and coordinating responses to health authority queries.
-Ability to maintain regulatory documentation, archival systems, and trackers.
-Experience preparing regulatory applications including clinical trial approvals, test licenses, amendments, renewals, HAQ responses.
-Ability to provide regulatory documentation support for tenders.
-Knowledge of dossier compilation and current Indian regulatory guidelines.
-Strong understanding of ethics, compliance, confidentiality, and governance expectations.
-Ability to support new product regulatory strategies and timely submissions.
-Experience collaborating with cross-functional teams and regional/international regulatory groups.
-Capability to manage compliance submissions, audits, deviations, and CAPAs.
-Experience supporting clinical trial submissions and lifecycle management.
-Ability to support packaging/artwork updates and local licensing.
-Skills in monitoring competitor regulatory trends and assessing business impacts.
-2–3 years of experience in Indian regulatory affairs.

