Job Description 30

Requirements:

-Ability to plan and develop procedures to ensure full regulatory compliance for the organization.
-Experience providing leadership to Regulatory and Quality departments, including establishing structures, systems, competencies, and compliance culture.
-Strong knowledge of national and international regulations, guidelines, and customer requirements to ensure product compliance in global markets.
-Capability to manage interfaces between Regulatory/Quality and cross-functional teams throughout product planning to securing government approvals.
-Skilled in monitoring and managing timelines for license applications, query responses, approvals, renewals, and regulatory submissions.
-Experience handling fresh and renewal applications, ethical committee clearances, predicate/non-predicate device registrations, legal metrology compliance, MRP compliance, voluntary/non-voluntary registrations, and medical device/IVD registrations.
-Ability to prepare, review, and oversee accurate submission dossiers in coordination with principals, regulatory partners, and distributors for India and global markets.
-Experience representing the organization before authorities such as CDSCO, DGHS, DAHD, DCA, FSSAI, CPCB, etc.
-Ability to maintain audit compliance and support internal/external audits.
-Skilled in managing post-marketing surveillance, Field Safety Corrective Actions (FSCA), follow-ups, documentation, and reporting.
-Ability to assess complaints for potential Reportable Events (pREs) and initiate required reporting.
-Experience managing recalls, investigations, documentation, and communication with Health Authorities.
-Ability to optimize, update, or establish SOPs for Regulatory functions.
-Experience supporting marketing with regulatory compliant input for promotional materials, packaging, labeling, flyers, and representative training.
-Strong ability to ensure effective communication and reporting systems within the Regulatory team.
-Experience coaching and mentoring Regulatory/Quality Associates on management and regulatory processes.
-Ability to manage the regulatory/quality budget and associated financial planning.
-Proven capability to ensure timely registration of all new products, devices, and instruments including licensing requirements.
-Ability to train cross-functional teams on regulatory requirements and compliance expectations.
-Experience ensuring all product specifications, documents, and procedures are maintained and up-to-date.
